title: The stink of death is coming from Jeb Bush
text: Posts: 4,440 The stink of death is coming from Jeb Bush The airwaves here are filled with Bush Ads, trying to get something going for the NH primary. But all that money can't even buy a dead cat bounce. If money won't move the meter, the money is going somewhere else. If Jeb doesn't break out of single digits, the money has got to reevaluate the field. Quote: Originally Posted by Camelot Citizens United will make Bush a shoe in to win the nomination. You folks just don't understand who makes such decisions in a Citizens United reality. Polls ? Really ? ï£¿ Location: nunya Posts: 3,060 That's what I smell? I thought it was cuz its deer season and I have not showered or shaved in 10 days Talent on loan from god Bush will be the Republican nominee. Originally Posted by Camelot Bush will be the Republican nominee. He's running all kinds of ads and his numbers aren't budging. That's what the money is supposed to do, let you run ads that boost your numbers. People, especially Republicans have already been disappointed by two Bushes, they don't want to go there again. Talent on loan from god Quote: Originally Posted by goober He's running all kinds of ads and his numbers aren't budging. That's what the money is supposed to do, let you run ads that boost your numbers. People, especially Republicans have already been disappointed by two Bushes, they don't want to go there again. Citizens United will make this decision. The media has fooled you. We are still a whole year out from the election. All the Republicans have is Bush, Rubio and Kasich. Rubio is a man-child joke and Kasich has been off the national stage too long. It will be Bush - Hillary. In time you will see that.
